  <title>WebKit2.CookieManager.prototype.set_persistent_storage</title>
  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
function set_persistent_storage(filename: String, storage: <link xref="WebKit2.CookiePersistentStorage">WebKit2.CookiePersistentStorage</link>): void {
    // Gjs wrapper for webkit_cookie_manager_set_persistent_storage()
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Set the <code>filename</code> where non-session cookies are stored persistently using
<code>storage</code> as the format to read/write the cookies.
Cookies are initially read from <code>filename</code> to create an initial set of cookies.
Then, non-session cookies will be written to <code>filename</code> when the WebKitCookieManager::changed
signal is emitted.
By default, <code>cookie_manager</code> doesn't store the cookies persistenly, so you need to call this
method to keep cookies saved across sessions.</p>

